# Docker Installation Guide

## Linux Installation (Ubuntu/Debian)

### Update Package Index
```bash
sudo apt-get update
```

### Install Required Packages
```bash
sudo apt-get install ca-certificates curl gnupg lsb-release
```

### Add Docker's Official GPG Key
```bash
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg
```

### Set Up Repository
```bash
echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
```

### Install Docker Engine
```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io
```

### Verify Installation
```bash
sudo docker run hello-world
```

### Add User to Docker Group (to run Docker without sudo)
```bash
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
```
*Note: Log out and back in for this to take effect*

## Linux Installation (CentOS/RHEL)

### Remove Old Versions (if any)
```bash
sudo yum remove docker docker-client docker-client-latest docker-common docker-latest docker-latest-logrotate docker-logrotate docker-engine
```

### Install Required Packages
```bash
sudo yum install -y yum-utils
```

### Set Up Repository
```bash
sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo
```

### Install Docker Engine
```bash
sudo yum install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io
```

### Start and Enable Docker
```bash
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
```

### Verify Installation
```bash
sudo docker run hello-world
```

### Add User to Docker Group
```bash
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
```
*Note: Log out and back in for this to take effect*

## Windows Installation

### System Requirements
- Windows 10 64-bit: Pro, Enterprise, or Education (Build 18362 or later)
- Windows 11 64-bit
- Enable Hyper-V and Containers Windows features

### Docker Desktop Installation

1. Download Docker Desktop from [Docker Hub](https://hub.docker.com/editions/community/docker-ce-desktop-windows/)

2. Double-click the downloaded installer (`Docker Desktop Installer.exe`)

3. Follow the installation wizard:
   - Enable Hyper-V Windows features when prompted
   - Allow the installer to log you out and restart if necessary

4. After restart, Docker Desktop will start automatically

### Verify Installation
Open PowerShell or Command Prompt and run:
```
docker --version
docker run hello-world
```

## Docker Compose Installation

### Linux
```bash
sudo curl -L "https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/v2.17.2/docker-compose-$(uname -s)-$(uname -m)" -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
```

### Verify Docker Compose Installation
```bash
docker-compose --version
```

### Windows
*Note: Docker Compose is included with Docker Desktop for Windows*
